title: Technology meets humanity at Swinburne
summary: Swinburne University of Technology is focused on impactful research that leverages technology to improve lives and promote sustainability. Various research projects at the university involve assisting elderly users with robots, enhancing cybersecurity through deep learning, app development for energy efficiency in homes, and studying legumes for sustainable agriculture. The university aims to connect technology development with social and environmental benefits, emphasizing a holistic approach to innovation.
green_innovation: TRUE, because the research projects mentioned contribute to environmental sustainability by promoting energy efficiency, enhancing social interaction among elderly users, and exploring sustainable agricultural practices which align with green innovation goals.
business_innovation: TRUE, because the developments highlighted involve new technological applications and methodologies that significantly differ from previous approaches and are aimed at the market and societal needs.
green_product: FALSE, because while the projects mentioned aim for sustainability, no specific product meeting the definition of a green product is explicitly identified in the article.
green_process: TRUE, because the processes related to energy efficiency app development and studying legumes for carbon mitigation aim to reduce environmental impacts, aligning with the definition of green processes.
likely_naics_codes: Likely NAICS Codes: 541712 - Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences; 541511 - Custom Computer Programming Services; 611310 - Colleges, Universities, and Professional Schools; 541620 - Environmental Consulting Services
greenwashing: FALSE, because the article does not present misleading information about the environmental benefits; instead, it discusses genuine efforts toward sustainability and innovation.
